{
  "stem": "71.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he-- once they sent rationed potatoes that came in to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they was laying outside, and they were not distributed to people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the rain came down, and they just fell apart.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They rotted.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- people started running to grab something, and they knew that people are going to get typhoid fever from it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, they poured Clorox on it, and they took-- and took it to, to graves, and threw it in the grave, and covered it up with [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A lot of people could have eaten that time, those potatoes, if they would be given, rationed out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I do blame Rumkowski very much.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a very stubborn man, and I knew-- I knew Rumkowski before the war-- from before the war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was an older man that took care on the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was going around collecting money.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's where I know him from.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He used to come to my father to collect money for that orphanage in Helenovek.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I knew him from coming year after year to our house, and my father used to support that orphanage.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He did an awful lot that time for the orphans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, in the ghetto, the one that was the Vermittler, they called him, the Bruder of the Juden-- the brother of the Jews-- the Germans used to call him.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He used to have everything that was going on between the Germans and the Jews, he took care-- He was raised in an orphanage, and Rumkowski made him like the head of the working class, you know that--",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, there was food coming in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Rumkowski said, once, he saved a few children, and [INAUDIBLE] my sister was working at that time, in a-- in a drugstore.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
